{"id":9612,"date":"2012-10-31T23:28:27","date_gmt":"2012-11-01T03:28:27","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=9612"},"modified":"2025-03-08T14:08:59","modified_gmt":"2025-03-08T10:08:59","slug":"sahaba-bayaa-not-ask-anyone","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/31\/sahaba-bayaa-not-ask-anyone\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Independence: Companions pledge not to ask from anyone"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>&#8216;Awf ibn Malik reported: We were with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, while there were seven, or eight, or nine of us. The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Will you not give your pledge to the Messenger of Allah?<\/strong>\u201d We had recently given our pledge, so we said, \u201cWe have given you our pledge of allegiance,\u201d but the Prophet said it again three times. We offered our hands and pledged allegiance to him again. Someone said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, we have already given you our pledge, so what are we pledging to now?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>That you worship Allah and do not associate any partners with him, that you pray for five prayers, that you listen and obey<\/strong>,\u201d and then the Prophet said something very softly, \u201c<strong>And that you do not ask people for anything<\/strong>.\u201d Indeed, some of those people obeyed this to the extent that if his whip were to fall from his mount, he would not ask anyone to hand it to him.<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1043<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Sahih<\/strong> <\/em>(authentic) according to Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u0646 \u0639\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0641 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064f\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0627 \u0639\u0650\u0646\u0652\u062f\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u06